      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 46
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Available is a 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the high-revving S54 3.2L inline-six engine, renowned for its individual throttle bodies and dual-VANOS high-pressure variable valve timing. This driver-spec example is equipped with the Getrag 6-speed manual gearbox and a torque-sensing M Variable Differential Lock. Mechanical highlights include a documented subframe reinforcement and proactive rod bearing replacement, ensuring structural rigidity and internal longevity. The chassis is dialed in with Bilstein B6 dampers and refreshed polyurethane bushings for precise turn-in and minimal lateral deflection. While the exterior shows minor road-going patina, the drivetrain remains optimized for peak volumetric efficiency and a visceral 8,000 RPM redline experience.",
